messages:
Name: Gökhan Gönül
Nationality: Turkey
Date of Birth: January 4, 1985
Position: Defender
Current club: Fenerbahçe
Süper Lig clubs played for: Gençlerbirliği, Fenerbahçe, Beşiktaş

Gökhan Gönül, the Fenerbahçe defender, has appeared in the majority of the team's Süper Lig matches in 2020/2021, making 21 appearances overall and playing 1,706 minutes. He has been selected in the starting XI in 19 of these appearances across their 40 fixtures and entered as a substitute on two occasions.

The last Süper Lig match that Gönül played came on May 11 for Fenerbahçe against Sivasspor; a match that he played 90 minutes in during a 2-1 defeat. In total, the defender has notched two Süper Lig goals in 2020/2021, and provided one assist. He has been booked four times, as well as sent off once.

Gönül was last on target in the league in the 2-0 win against Denizlispor on December 6, netting in the 40th minute. He opened his account for the campaign against Rizespor on September 11, scoring during a 2-1 victory.
Gönül played 30 Süper Lig games last season for Beşiktaş, scored four goals and provided three assists.
Gönül switched to Fenerbahçe in August 2020 from Beşiktaş, for whom he made 113 league appearances in total, scoring eight goals and providing nine assists.
